==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Parabanic
<hw>Par`a*ban"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ to pass
over.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Pertaining to, or designating, a
nitrogenous acid which is obtained by the oxidation of uric acid, as a
white crystalline substance (<chform>C3N2H2O3</chform>); -- also called
<xex>oxalyl urea</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

